  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was purely a Flemish-speaking village, and those children belonged to homes, were either French or Yiddish, and because of the Yiddish-- French with a Yiddish accent, or whatever-- very little Flemish was spoken.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that gave them-- gave them automatically away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember that a few months later when the Roggemans, under my mother's instructions, who supplied her money, had found a private school run by not-- official school we couldn't go to-- state school.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Private school run by-- was a French school, it was called, Institut Les Abeilles, the bees, and it was about a few kilometers away from where we were living near the city hall of this other suburb called, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and-- and then-- and we were, they accepted us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Matter of fact, a very interesting-- they knew that we were Jewish, but they were very patriotic people because that was a private French school, and the-- the principal had been a very patriotically lady, so she had the French flag flying on the school.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the Germans told her that she had to take the French flag down, and had to have a swastika, German flag in all schools and buildings, but you could not-- you could not show any flag other than the German flag.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had been very patriotic, refused to take it down.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she was, although she was a Christian herself, she was deported and spend five years in a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So her daughter, [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Mrs.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Paulette, ?] took over the school, running of the school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she was very, very anti the authorities, and conducive to-- to-- to-- to let Jewish kids come in, as long as there was money to pay for them.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
